Reasoning: The paper describes the development of a digital histopathology system using deep learning for identifying odontogenic keratocysts in hematoxylin- and eosin-stained tissue specimens of jaw cysts. This involves image analysis and classification, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for training and classification also suggests that the paper falls under the deep learning (cs.DL) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Finally, the use of microscopy images and digital scanning for analysis suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
